I am a fundamentally curiosity driven individual. My interests include plant and animal phylogenetics and systematics, community ecology, plant ecophysiology, and the effects of climate change on the worlds biota. I enjoy applying numerically and statistically grounded methods in these fields. My long-term goals are careers in research, academia, and teaching.

MSc candidate (Dept. of Biological Sciences, University of Cape Town) (2018present).
